HEADWORD: Snooze
<hw>Snooze</hw> <pr>(sn⟦oomac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot.
<ets>snooze</ets> to sleep; cf. Dan. & Sw. <ets>snus</ets> snuff.]</ety>
<def>A short sleep; a nap.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

